# Esiana Backend

Applies when editing `backend/`. See [phase-10-ecosystem.md](../../docs/plugins/phase-10-ecosystem.md).

## Campaign routing

- Primary scoped surface: `/api/campaigns/:handle/*` (CRUD remains `/api/campaigns/:id`)
- Use `resolveCampaignScope` / `requireCampaignMembership` patterns
- Mutations: `findFirst({ id, campaignId })` then `update({ where: { id } })`

## Domain events

- `dispatchDomainEvent` — DTOs only, no Prisma delegates or raw wiki block payloads
- Core types: `core:wiki:*`, `core:notebook_arc:*`, `core:calendar:advanced`
- Non-blocking fan-out; plugins emit with `{pluginId}:` prefix
- Extend direct controller hooks; do not centralize all emitters in one refactor

## API bearer tokens

- Respect `scopes`; session auth bypasses scope checks
- Empty scopes = legacy full access — do not expand legacy behavior for new routes

## Uploads & media

- ACL-backed `GET /uploads/:filename` and `GET /api/assets/:id`
- No static public upload directories
- Private cache headers for campaign-scoped assets

## Map scene APIs

- Party payloads: omit hidden objects entirely (no placeholders, no `reason`)
- Clamp party `viewEpochMinute` to `Campaign.currentEpochMinute`
- Strip link targets when target wiki page is not viewable
- `resolveMapObjectPresence` must not read `groupId` for visibility

## New models

- Stay Prisma-portable; consider export/backup impact in campaign ZIP flows
